                <h2>Why We Procrastinate</h2>
                <p><em>Understanding the psychology behind procrastination</em></p>
            </header>
            <p>Procrastination is often a result of <mark>psychological barriers</mark> like fear of failure or perfectionism. Many people delay tasks not because they are lazy, but because they feel overwhelmed or unsure where to start.</p>
            <details>
                <summary>Click to learn more</summary>
                <p>Studies show that setting small, achievable goals can help reduce procrastination.</p>
